    think='The issue with the tests is that `expectLater` is called AFTER `bloc.
emit()`, which means some events might be missed. In `flutter_bloc`, `emit()` im
mediately notifies listeners, so if `expectLater` is called after `emit()`, it m
isses the initial state.\n\nWait, actually `expectLater` listens to `bloc.stream
`, which is a broadcast stream of state changes. When you call `bloc.emit(state)
`, it adds to the stream. If `expectLater` starts listening after `emit()`, it s
hould still receive future emissions. But the problem might be that `expectLater
` doesn\'t catch emissions that happen synchronously during its setup.\n\nActual
ly, looking at the error message:\n```\nExpected: should do the following in ord
er:\n          • emit an event that <Instance of \'MatchingMatchCreated\'>\n    
