ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="The tests are failing because `expectLater` with `emitsInOrder` doesn
't work well when the bloc emits multiple states in quick succession, especially
when using `bloc.emit()` directly in tests. The `ExternalMatchReceived` and `Mat
chModalDismissed` tests are timing out because `expectLater` listens to the stre
am but the events have already been emitted before the listener is set up.\n\nAl
so, the first `ExternalMatchReceived` test shows that after `MatchingMatchCreate
d`, the stream closed before `MatchingLoadSuccess` was emitted. This is because 
`bloc.emit()` in tests doesn't always work as expected with `expectLater`.\n\nI 
need to fix these tests. The issue is that when using `bloc.emit()` to set the i
nitial state and then `bloc.add()` to trigger an event, `expectLater` might miss
the events.\n\nLet me fix the tests by using a different pattern - instead of `e
xpectLater`, I can use `blocTest` from `bloc_test` package, but it's not in pubs
pec. Alternatively, I can use `expectLater` with a seed state or just listen to 
the stream first before adding events.\n\nActually, the proper way to test blocs
without `bloc_test` is:\n1. Start listening to the stream FIRST with `expectLate
r`\n2. THEN add events\n\nThe current code does `bloc.emit(...)` and THEN `bloc.
add(...)` and THEN `expectLater`. That won't work because the stream listener mi
sses the events.\n\nLet me restructure the tests.",
    encrypted=None
)
