ce of \'_BroadcastStream<MatchingState>\'>\n Which: emitted • MatchingMatchCreat
ed(MatchSummary(matchId: match-1, conversationId: conv-1, matchedUser: MatchedUs
er(userId: u2, nickname: Bob, avatarUrl: null), createdAt: 2026-04-22T07:49:21.9
85230))\n                x Stream closed.\n```\n\n"Stream closed" means the bloc
was closed before `MatchingLoadSuccess` was emitted. Wait, that shouldn\'t happe
n because `tearDown` only runs after the test completes.\n\nOh wait - `expectLat
er` might be completing early when it sees `MatchingMatchCreated`, and then the 
test ends, triggering `tearDown` which closes the bloc. Then `MatchingLoadSucces
s` is emitted on a closed bloc, which is ignored.\n\nActually no, `expectLater` 
with `emitsInOrder` should wait for all expected events. But if the stream close
s before all events are emitted, it fails.\n\nLooking at the `_onExternalMatchRe
ceived` handler:\n```dart\nvoid _onExternalMatchReceived(\n  ExternalMatchReceiv
ed event,\n  Emitter<MatchingState> emit,\n) {\n  emit(MatchingMatchCreated(even
t.matchSummary));\n  final currentState = state;\n  if (currentState is Matching
LoadSuccess) {\n    emit(MatchingLoadSuccess(\n        cards: currentState.cards
, mode: currentState.mode));\n  } else if (currentState is MatchingLoadEmpty) {\
n    emit(MatchingLoadEmpty(mode: currentState.mode));\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe probl
em is that after `emit(MatchingMatchCreated(event.matchSummary))`, the state bec
omes `MatchingMatchCreated`, not `MatchingLoadSuccess`. So the `if (currentState
is MatchingLoadSuccess)` check fails because `state` is now `MatchingMatchCreate
d`.\n\nThis is a bug in the original bloc code! The handler reads `state` after 
emitting, but `state` has already changed to the newly emitted state. This means
`MatchingLoadSuccess` is never emitted after `MatchingMatchCreated` in `_onExter
nalMatchReceived`.\n\nSimilarly in `_onMatchModalDismissed`:\n```dart\nvoid _onM
atchModalDismissed(\n  MatchModalDismissed event,\n  Emitter<MatchingState> emit
,\n) {\n  final currentState = state;\n  if (currentState is MatchingLoadSuccess
) {\n    emit(MatchingLoadSuccess(\n        cards: currentState.cards, mode: cur
rentState.mode));\n  } else if (currentState is MatchingLoadEmpty) {\n    emit(M
atchingLoadEmpty(mode: currentState.mode));\n  }\n}\n```\n\nIf the current state
is `MatchingLoadSuccess`, this should work. But in the test, I set the state wit
h `bloc.emit(...)` and then call `bloc.add(MatchModalDismissed())`. The `expectL
ater` listens after `emit()`, so when `MatchModalDismissed` is processed, `state
` should be `MatchingLoadSuccess`.\n\nWait, but in the test error for MatchModal
Dismissed:\n```\nExpected: should emit an event that <Instance of \'MatchingLoad
Success\'> with `cards length`: <1>\nActual: <Instance of \'_BroadcastStream<Mat
chingState>\'>\n Which: emitted x Stream closed.\n```\n\n"Stream closed" - this 
suggests the bloc was closed before anything was emitted. But why?\n\nActually, 
looking at the test more carefully, `expectLater` returns a Future. If we `await
expectation` at the end, it should work. But the issue might be that `bloc.emit(
)` is called before `expectLater`, and `expectLater` misses the initial state. B
ut `expectLater` only checks future emissions, not the current state.\n\nOh wait
! In the `ExternalMatchReceived` test, `expectLater` does receive `MatchingMatch
Created` but then the stream closes. Why does the stream close? Because the test
`tearDown` closes the bloc. But `tearDown` should only run after `await expectat
ion` completes.\n\nHmm, unless `expectLater` completes as soon as it sees `Match
ingMatchCreated` because there\'s a bug in the stream. Actually, `emitsInOrder` 
expects exactly the listed events and then the stream to close. So if the stream
closes after `MatchingMatchCreated` but before `MatchingLoadSuccess`, the test f
ails.\n\nBut why would the stream close? Unless the bloc is being closed prematu
rely. Or maybe `expectLater` itself causes issues.\n\nActually wait - `bloc.stre
am` is a broadcast stream. When `expectLater` subscribes, it gets future events.
If the bloc doesn\'t emit `MatchingLoadSuccess`, then eventually the test times 
out because `expectLater` is waiting for it.\n\nSo the real issue is that `_onEx
ternalMatchReceived` doesn\'t emit `MatchingLoadSuccess` because after `emit(Mat
chingMatchCreated(...))`, `state` is `MatchingMatchCreated`, not `MatchingLoadSu
ccess`.\n\nI need to fix the MatchingBloc. In `_onExternalMatchReceived`, I shou
ld save the current state BEFORE emitting, or change the logic.\n\nLet me fix th
e bloc code.',
