ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="The `MatchModalDismissed` test is still timing out. The issue is that
in `_onMatchModalDismissed`, when the current state is `MatchingLoadSuccess` (wh
ich was set via `bloc.emit()`), the handler emits `MatchingLoadSuccess` again. B
ut since the emitted state is identical to the current state (same cards, same m
ode), `flutter_bloc` deduplicates it and doesn't emit it to the stream.\n\n`flut
ter_bloc` only emits states if `state != newState` (using `==`). Since `Matching
LoadSuccess` extends `Equatable` and has the same props, it won't be emitted.\n\
nSo the `expectLater` waits forever for `MatchingLoadSuccess` but it never comes
because it's deduplicated.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Not test `MatchModalDismisse
d` with identical state\n2. Or change the test expectation\n3. Or make the bloc 
emit a different state and then re-emit\n\nActually, the simplest fix is to not 
expect `MatchingLoadSuccess` in the test if the state is the same. The `MatchMod
alDismissed` event is meant to dismiss the modal and return to the previous stat
e. If the state is already `MatchingLoadSuccess`, the bloc doesn't need to emit 
anything.\n\nLet me update the test to not expect any emission when the state is
unchanged. Or better, I can test it by first emitting `MatchingMatchCreated` and
then calling `MatchModalDismissed`.\n\nActually, looking at the real flow: when 
a match is created, the state becomes `MatchingMatchCreated`. Then `MatchModalDi
smissed` should transition back to `MatchingLoadSuccess` or `MatchingLoadEmpty`.
\n\nLet me fix the test to reflect this real flow.",
    encrypted=None
)
